BT
/F1 11 Tf
/F1 18 Tf
72 742 Td (4. TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
72 704 Td (Frontend: The Android application is developed using Kotlin and XML layouts in Android) Tj
72 689 Td (Studio. The user interface is high-contrast and simple so that farmers can use it easily) Tj
72 674 Td (in field conditions.) Tj
72 651 Td (Swipe Experience: ViewPager2 is used for the flash-card swipe interface. Farmers can) Tj
72 636 Td (move between advisory cards by swiping left or right.) Tj
72 613 Td (Database: Room Database is used to store daily farming tips locally. This allows the app) Tj
72 598 Td (to show saved tips even when internet connectivity is not available.) Tj
72 575 Td (Media: Glide is used to load crop and pest-related images into the advisory cards.) Tj
72 552 Td (Networking: Retrofit and Gson Converter are used to connect the Android app with the) Tj
72 537 Td (backend REST API.) Tj
72 514 Td (Backend: A Node.js backend server is implemented without external npm packages. It) Tj
72 499 Td (provides APIs for tips, expert requests, expert replies, and a browser dashboard.) Tj
72 476 Td (Storage: Expert Ask requests are saved in a JSON file named expert-asks.json so that) Tj
72 461 Td (they remain available even after backend restart.) Tj
ET

endstream
endobj
